			<p><span class="smallcaps"><strong>Michelle Cacho-Negrete</strong></span> is a retired psychotherapist who lives in Maine. She&rsquo;s won the Hope Award for her writing and been nominated three times for a Pushcart Prize. She works with writing students in person and online, and holds a five-day writing workshop in Maine every spring, after the snow and before the black flies.</p><a href="/contributors/michelle-cacho-negrete" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
